des Schönen“ auf die Sprachursprungshypothese.Das Buch ergänzt damit die Disziplingeschichte der Linguistik um einen eigenwilligen Sprachforscher und erfüllt, indem es Moritz' Sprachschriften in den Kontext des Gesamtwerkes stellt, eine seit 20 Jahren erhobene Forderung der Moritzforschung. „Die Sprache und das Schöne“ zeigt Moritz in einem neuen Licht.  aKarl Philipp Moritz is best known as the author of the novel Anton Reiser, and as a scholar of classical aesthetics. However, there is another area of his work that was extremely important to him: his engagement with language. Against the backdrop of European intellectual history, this book spotlights Moritz as an original grammarian and philosopher of language. It also illustrates the ways that his reflections on language helped develop the methods of thinking that later became the foundation for his aesthetics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAesthetics, Germany18th century. 0aGerman languagexAesthetics. 0aLinguisticsxPhilosophyy18th century. 4aHistorische Grammatik. 4aLinguistik. 4aMoritz, Karl Philipp. 4aSprachphilosophie. 4aÄsthetik. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / German.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aHistorical Grammar.  aLinguistic Philosophy.  aLinguistics.  aMoritz, Karl Philipp.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311028969540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028989340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110289893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/